Description:
Luxurious near-new home with sophisticated appeal
Skip the stress of building and move straight in to your near-new, luxuriously appointed home!
This beautifully designed three bedroom abode will exceed your expectations.
Set in idyllic Carlotta Place, the north-facing home overlooks landscaped parkland and enjoys a quiet outlook with very little through traffic.
The interior feels contemporary and grand, with neutral tones that compliment any colour scheme. Heightened ceilings and doorways amplify space, and natural light floods every room. Windows throughout are finished with elegant shutter style blinds.
At the heart of the home, the open plan kitchen/living/dining hub has a light and airy feel. You'll enjoy easy access to the private backyard and undercover decked entertaining area via sliding stacker doors, which retract to provide an expansive indoor/outdoor living zone. Light is easily filtered and privacy maintained with stylish sliding panel glide blinds.
The central chef's kitchen overlooks the living space, dining and alfresco areas. Extravagant 40mm Caesarstone benchtops will impress, and stainless steel appliances include a 900mm Technika electric oven with gas cooktop, glass canopy rangehood and Bellissimo dishwasher. The island bench with breakfast bar is ideal for informal dining. The spacious walk-in pantry houses the fridge, and hides the clutter!
The rear of the home boasts an expansive and private master suite. It features a fully fitted walk-through robe with 'His' and 'Hers' sections, plus a light-filled and contemporary ensuite. Luxurious inclusions, such as the double shower with rain head and hand-held rose and the soft-close toilet, mean you may never want to leave!
The two large queen-size bedrooms include built-in robes with sliding doors and are near the central bathroom, which features a large floating vanity, huge shower, niche cut-out, and a deep luxurious bath.
A separate lounge (or optional 4th bedroom) speaks of uninterrupted TV viewing and quiet time overlooking the park.
The laundry is generous with plenty of storage and direct backyard access. The property also features a double lock-up garage with secure internal access.
The backyard is private, secure and elegantly landscaped with lush lawn, bluestone pavers and Lilydale toppings.
Additional features include ducted gas heating throughout, reverse-cycle air-conditioning to the living areas, endless gas/solar hot water and fibre optic cabling installed for high-speed Internet and flawless TV reception.
A contemporary and luxurious home for convenient, easy living!
- Set on quiet lane with little through traffic, adjacent to parkland and extra OSP
- 3 BRs, master with walk-through robe and ensuite, others with BIRs
- Open plan kitchen/living/dining adjoins alfresco and backyard
- Separate lounge (or 4th BR) for quiet time or dedicated TV viewing
- Sleek wet areas with contemporary decor and large showers, main bathroom with bath
- DLUG, ducted heating, RC AC, endless gas/solar hot water and fibre optic cabling
Land: 400 sq m approx.

Description:
Nalbra Estate - Lifestyle Property with Commanding Vineyard and Bay Views
Under Instructions From Merc Property Consultants. Nalbra Estate (6 acres, 2.43ha) is an award winning, boutique vineyard perched on Mount Bellarine with commanding views across Port Phillip Bay. 3.5 acres of vineyard, established in black cracking, self-mulching clay, produces fruit with intense richness and colour. Varieties include 1.5 acres Shiraz, 1.5 acres Sauvignon Blanc, 0.4 acres Pinot Gris and 220 Viongnier vines. Sought-after produce has been awarded at the 2010 Geelong Wines Show and in the 2012 James Halliday Wine Companion.
The homestead (4 bedrooms and 3 living areas) has a U-shaped design that wraps around a Japanese water garden courtyard. There are sunny courtyards and shady veranda nooks, manicured gardens, specimen trees and rolling lawns.
Indoors, solid hardwood features denote quality. The floor plan offers a wing for parents, children and a living and entertaining wing. Parent's wing with spacious lounge, 2 BRs with robes, wet area and study. Children's wing with sitting room, 2 BRs with robes, shower room, bathroom, large office and laundry. Open plan living and entertaining flows to a protected sundrenched courtyard. Kitchen with island bench and hardwood cabinetry. Separate exposed brick cellar/larder.
Central heating and cooling. Detached DLUG with workshop.
31,500L above ground and 45,000L underground tanks plus town water.
5 minutes to Drysdale, 25 minutes to Geelong and 90 minutes to Melbourne. Close to well-renowned schools.
Make a bid on this sophisticated lifestyle property!

Description:
Blantyre" - Productive acres between the Bays
Like its namesake in Scotland, meaning "top of the land", this property, sited between Corio Bay and Swan Bay and surrounded by beautiful rural vistas, is indeed 'tops'!
The property boasts 82 acres (approx) (33.12ha) of fertile ground and 3 dams, ideal for cropping or livestock and is bound by established shelter belts with glimpses of Swan Bay from the Victorian 3 bedroom homestead.
The driveway is lined with majestic gums and provides a welcoming approach. The charming porch takes you back in time setting the theme for the home's interior. Beautiful decor includes stained glass, iron lace, original tongue-and-groove wood panelling, timber windows and lofty ceilings.
The bedrooms are queen-sized, one with an original period-style open fireplace.
The central living and dining space is open plan and flooded with easterly sunlight. These windows capture wide countryside views framed by the iron lace of the adjoining veranda. Swan Bay glimpses linger on the horizon. A Rinnai gas heater assists comfort.
The galley-style kitchen is linked to the living/dining space via a servery, and features electric cooking appliances, spacious benches and good storage.
The wet area offers a shower, vanity and toilet.
Outhouses include a roomy bunkhouse, washhouse with 2nd toilet, vintage tractor shed for 2 vehicles, modern machinery shed for 3 vehicles and a hay shed.
Servicing the homestead is a 6800L water tank and a septic system.
Ripe for renovation, this home could be a rewarding project for those with a passion for restoration. Otherwise, the land provides ample room and a stunning rural setting for your ultimate home build.
5 minutes to Drysdale, 15 minutes to beaches, 30 minutes to Geelong and 90 minutes to Melbourne. Developers may investigate subdivision potential (STCA).
This fertile land parcel has a special feel. Surrounded by successful local producers, country cafes and wineries, it's a great place to establish a convenient rural lifestyle! View ASAP!
- 81.84 stunning and fertile acres (33.12ha) between Corio Bay and Swan Bay
- Victorian 3BR homestead with stained glass, iron lace, tongue-and-groove timber panelling and lofty ceilings
- Bright, open plan living/dining with Swan Bay glimpses through floor-to-ceiling windows
- Bunkhouse, washhouse, old tractor shed for 2, machinery shed for 3 and hay shed
- 3 dams
- 6800L water tank to house and septic tank
- 5 mins to Drysdale, 15 mins to beaches, 30 mins to Geelong, 90 mins to Melbourne
Land: 82 Acress approx.

Description:
Elegant, Luxurious and Spacious Family Residence.
This stunning 2 year old four bedroom builder's private residence, offers outstanding space for family living and entertaining, situated on an impressive 670 sqm (approx.) allotment in a premier location. The casual sophistication and elegance of this offering is immediately apparent upon entry, with high open ceilings, stacked stone wall and open plan living. Leading from the entrance you will find the theatre room and study/forth bedroom and access to the alfresco entertaining and private yard off the open plan living. Abundant light spills through the clear storey windows into the exceptional open plan living/dining/kitchen area, featuring the gorgeous gas fireplace retaining the relaxing feel of the house. The brilliantly appointed kitchen offers the finest quality Siemens appliances in addition to integrated D/W and refrigerator along with superb Caesar stone bench tops and a large butler's pantry. The spacious walk in robe and en-suite accompany the huge master bedroom, with a further two generous bedrooms complete with built in robes and central bathroom, perfect for the family unit. Downstairs offers yet another integrated entertaining space with access to a bathroom, outside and direct entry into the triple garage. Additional features include Intercom and alarm system with LED screen, double glazed commercial windows, electric security gate, LED lights throughout and ducted vacuum. A home built to impress, enjoys an easy walk to McLeod's Waterholes, Drysdale shops and cafes and public transport.

Description:
THE PERFECT DOWNSIZER WITH ROOM FOR CARAVAN
Located close to central Drysdale, this modern home on approx 610m2 of land is the perfect downsizer. Comprising 3 bedrooms, central bathroom, open plan living/dining with a galley style kitchen opening onto a rear balcony to take in the sunset view. Features Tasmanian Oak timber floors, ducted gas heating, split system cooling, and a single garage with remote door along with low maintenance yards and side/rear yard access for the boat, caravan or trailer. Outside a water tank fitted with a rain flush system that supplies the toilet, washing machine and outside tap, switching over to town water when required. The perfect downsizer.

Description:
Out of the pages of House & Garden
This wonderful light and bright home's focus is indoor and outdoor living. Rich timbers are displayed throughout flooring and windows, with white walls creating a bright, light filled home with real warmth.
The kitchen offers gorgeous Blackwood timber bench tops, dishwasher and substantial walk in butler's pantry. Formal lounge & dining area. An additional step down spacious sun filled living area with high ceilings opens out to verandah entertaining area overlooking the generous backyard with paved courtyard area under sunshade.
Upstairs consists entirely of the parents retreat/master suite, complimented by ample windows with wooden shutters, large walk in robe and ensuite.
All remaining bedrooms are located downstairs along with the laundry and central bathroom.
Features include central heating, dishwasher, loads of storage (including large walk in linen cupboard), elevated decks, manicured gardens (including side walkway garden near fernery), front & rear verandah areas and quality throughout. Side drive with carport to double freestanding garage. Additional separate rear access.
All this on a generous 799m2 (approx) allotment.

Description:
1960's HOUSE BUILT TO LAST
This home has only had one family own it since it was built in 1960 and now they have decided to give someone else the opportunity to enjoy all that Drysdale has to offer. Many family memories are kept within these walls. Boasting a land size of 1175m2 (approx) with a 90' (27.4m) frontage,this home could be enjoyed by a family who want some space or by a developer who has a vision for change.
Room to expand this well built home or to leave it and change the landscape all together and do something totally new are all options open to this three bedroom, one living, one bathroom home. As was the era of the day the rooms are all very spacious.
The Drysdale Township is a short walk away. Drysdale was established in the late 1840's and although things have progressed around it the town still has a country feel.
What are you waiting for?

Description:
New home with an open design for modern living
Carlotta Place, in the new Curlewis Park Estate, is an idyllic lane where all homes view land scaped parkland with walking trail and adventure playground. It has little through traffic and extra off street parking bays, and is a terrific locale to extend your living outside of your own allotment. Close to Drysdale shops and the boat ramp, this home will appeal to small families, investors and down sizes.
With sharp lines and neutral colour tones the fresh façade is contemporary. The solid brick build boasts a tiled roof and twin pillars which frame the entrance porch.
The home unfolds off the central hallway, with vision from the front door through to the backyard. Glossy hallway tiles reflect natural light. The living areas and study have an open plan design and a light, airy feel. All rooms are centrally linked, yet privacy is maintained in bedrooms and wet areas.
The lounge sits off the entry and is graced with the striking horizontal and vertical façade glazing. This space speaks of uninterrupted TV viewing and quiet time. The study nook is ideally located for homework and book keeping.
At the rear, the meals area, kitchen and living space flow end to end, terminating in a glass slider to the backyard. The chef is central to the action, with great culinary tools, and can oversee the TV in the living space and diners in the meals area. Stainless steel appliances include; Bellissima oven, cooktop and range hood and LG dishwasher. The long island bench with breakfast bar is ideal for informal dining and chit chat.
Wet areas are sleek and unused with a fresh neutral colour scheme. Timber effect vanities hold chunky square basins and showers boasts in situ floors. The main bathroom has a separate bath and shower. The master bedroom is private with walk-in robe and en suite. Two further bedrooms boast built-in robes and flow from the living space. The laundry is bright with a glass slider to the yard.
Ducted heating and cooling throughout. Fibre optic cabling to the estate.
The double lock-up garage features internal and backyard accesses. The backyard is safe and secure; a blank canvas ready for personalisation.
A contemporary home for convenient easy living! View and realise the beauty of its location!
* Set on quiet lane adjacent to parkland with playground, extra OSP and little through traffic
* 3 BRs, master with WIR and en suite, others with BIRs
* Open plan meals/kitchen/dining with yard access and stainless steel appliances
* Separate lounge and study for dedicated TV viewing and book keeping
* Sleek, unused wet areas with neutral colour scheme and in situ showers; main with bath
* DLUG, ducted heating and cooling, fibre optic cabling to the estate
Terms: 10% deposit, balance 30/60 days
Land: 400 sq m approx.
